<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 13:27:17 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>IL-4治疗诱导血液单核细胞凋亡和招募的损伤相关巨噬细胞增殖以解决肝损伤</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/il-4-treatment-induces-apoptosis-of-blood-monocytes-and-proliferation-of-recruited-injury-associated-macrophages-to-resolve-liver-injury</link><description>有利于免疫细胞向具有治愈潜力的细胞平衡的途径为损伤后提供了治疗希望。在这里，林奇等人。研究表明，IL-4 治疗可通过增殖扩大促修复巨噬细胞，同时驱动其炎症性前体细胞同时死亡，从而加速急性肝损伤后的肝修复。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/il-4-treatment-induces-apoptosis-of-blood-monocytes-and-proliferation-of-recruited-injury-associated-macrophages-to-resolve-liver-injury2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 13:27:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/il-4-treatment-induces-apoptosis-of-blood-monocytes-and-proliferation-of-recruited-injury-associated-macrophages-to-resolve-liver-injury</guid></item><item><title>IL-9 和 Blimp-1 保护过敏性哮喘中 2 组先天淋巴细胞的转录特性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/il-9-and-blimp-1-protect-the-transcriptional-identity-of-group-2-innate-lymphocytes-in-allergic-asthma</link><description>开放访问。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/il-9-and-blimp-1-protect-the-transcriptional-identity-of-group-2-innate-lymphocytes-in-allergic-asthma.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 13:12:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/il-9-and-blimp-1-protect-the-transcriptional-identity-of-group-2-innate-lymphocytes-in-allergic-asthma</guid></item><item><title>总统年龄辩论掩盖了一个简单的事实：随着年龄的增长，一些认知技能会提高</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/presidential-age-debate-obscures-a-simple-fact-some-cognitive-skills-improve-as-we-get-older</link><description>虽然心理处理速度等一些技能会随着年龄的增长而下降，但其他认知技能对于 70 多岁及以上的老年人来说会有所改善。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/presidential-age-debate-obscures-a-simple-fact-some-cognitive-skills-improve-as-we-get-older2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 12:57:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/presidential-age-debate-obscures-a-simple-fact-some-cognitive-skills-improve-as-we-get-older</guid></item><item><title>胸腺非典型类癌：病例报告中的早期诊断</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/atypical-carcinoid-of-the-thymus-early-diagnosis-in-a-case-report</link><description>背景：胸腺非典型类癌是一种极其罕见的神经内分泌肿瘤，起源于胸腺内的神经内分泌细胞。这些肿瘤通常没有任何症状或具有非特异性临床体征，使得早期诊断特别具有挑战性。尽管罕见，非典型类癌因其侵袭性和相对较差的预后而具有临床意义。因此，早期发现和适当的管理对于改善患者的治疗效果至关重要。结果：在本报告中，我们介绍了一名 64 岁患者的病例，该患者因无关原因进行胸部计算机断层扫描后偶然发现了非典型胸腺类癌。影像学检查发现可疑的前纵隔肿块，随后进行了手术切除。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/atypical-carcinoid-of-the-thymus-early-diagnosis-in-a-case-report2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 12:42:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/atypical-carcinoid-of-the-thymus-early-diagnosis-in-a-case-report</guid></item><item><title>将微生物群应用于临床癌症免疫治疗的机遇和挑战</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/opportunities-and-challenges-in-applying-microbiota-to-clinical-cancer-immunotherapy</link><description>临床癌症免疫治疗中的微生物群。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/opportunities-and-challenges-in-applying-microbiota-to-clinical-cancer-immunotherapy2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 12:27:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/opportunities-and-challenges-in-applying-microbiota-to-clinical-cancer-immunotherapy</guid></item><item><title>NASA 望远镜数据中发现 10,000 颗新行星</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/10000-new-planets-found-hidden-in-nasa-telescope-data</link><description>NASA 的凌日系外行星勘测卫星自 2018 年发射以来一直在寻找系外行星，事实证明它发现的系外行星可能比我们想象的要多得多&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/10000-new-planets-found-hidden-in-nasa-telescope-data.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 12:12:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/10000-new-planets-found-hidden-in-nasa-telescope-data</guid></item><item><title>VirtuCamera 2 已到货</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/virtucamera-2-has-arrived</link><description>虽然已经过去很长时间了，但等待终于结束了。如果你还不熟悉的话&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/virtucamera-2-has-arrived.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 11:57:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/virtucamera-2-has-arrived</guid></item><item><title>氧化应激诱导的星形胶质细胞胶原生物合成驱动缺血性中风中神经胶质屏障的形成和神经元死亡</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/oxidative-stress-induced-astrocytic-collagen-biosynthesis-drives-glial-barrier-formation-and-neuronal-death-in-ischemic-stroke</link><description>现已上线：Lee 等人。证明氧化应激会通过糖基化依赖性机制重新编程星形胶质细胞产生胶原蛋白，从而驱动神经胶质屏障的形成和中风后进行性神经元死亡。针对该通路可破坏神经胶质屏障，防止神经退行性变，并改善功能恢复。候选药物 KDS12025 在非人类灵长类中风模型中显示出有效的效果。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/oxidative-stress-induced-astrocytic-collagen-biosynthesis-drives-glial-barrier-formation-and-neuronal-death-in-ischemic-stroke2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 11:42:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/oxidative-stress-induced-astrocytic-collagen-biosynthesis-drives-glial-barrier-formation-and-neuronal-death-in-ischemic-stroke</guid></item><item><title>为什么新生儿的记忆回路一开始很拥挤，然后随着大脑的成熟而变细</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/why-newborn-memory-circuits-start-crowded-then-slim-down-as-brains-mature</link><description>海马体是参与记忆形成和空间定向的关键大脑区域。它将短期记忆转化为长期记忆，帮助我们保留并巩固我们的经验。奥地利科学技术研究所 (ISTA) 生命科学教授彼得·乔纳斯 (Peter Jonas) 领导的研究人员正是专注于大脑的这一区域。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-newborn-memory-circuits-start-crowded-then-slim-down-as-brains-mature2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 11:27:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/why-newborn-memory-circuits-start-crowded-then-slim-down-as-brains-mature</guid></item><item><title>研究发现，群体平均值掩盖了个体大脑如何控制行为</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/group-averages-obscure-how-an-individuals-brain-controls-behavior-study-finds</link><description>斯坦福大学医学院的新研究表明，通过平均许多人的大脑扫描数据来研究认知隐藏了个人如何使用他们的大脑。特别是，当对那些努力完成以目标为导向的任务的孩子的数据进行单独分析时，而不是作为一群具有混合能力的孩子的一部分时，他们会表现出独特的大脑活动模式。这些发现对于理解大脑在注意力缺陷/多动症等情况下如何工作具有重要意义，将于 4 月 27 日发表在《自然通讯》上。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/group-averages-obscure-how-an-individuals-brain-controls-behavior-study-finds2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 11:12:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/group-averages-obscure-how-an-individuals-brain-controls-behavior-study-finds</guid></item></channel></rss>